cause_icd10: The crude death rate (CDR) is the number of deaths registered during the year per 100,000 estimated resident population at 30 June.
cause_name: The crude death rate (CDR) is the number of deaths registered during the year per 100,000 estimated resident population at 30 June.

cause_icd10: Standardised death rates (SDRs) enable the comparison of death rates between populations with different age structures by relating them to a standard population. The current standard population is all persons in the Australian population at 30 June 2001.
cause_name: Standardised death rates (SDRs) enable the comparison of death rates between populations with different age structures by relating them to a standard population. The current standard population is all persons in the Australian population at 30 June 2001.

cause_icd10: Death Rates and Years of Potential Life Lost (YPLL) based on small numbers are volatile and unreliable. SDRs based on less than 20 deaths and crude rates or YPLL based on a very low death count have not been published and appear as 'np'.

cause_icd10: The crude death rate (CDR) is the number of deaths registered during the year per 100,000 estimated resident population at 30 June.

cause_icd10: Standardised death rates (SDRs) enable the comparison of death rates between populations with different age structures by relating them to a standard population. The current standard population is all persons in the Australian population at 30 June 2001.

cause_icd10: The crude death rate (CDR) is the number of deaths registered during the year per 100,000 estimated resident population at 30 June.
cause_name: The crude death rate (CDR) is the number of deaths registered during the year per 100,000 estimated resident population at 30 June.

cause_icd10: Standardised death rates (SDRs) enable the comparison of death rates between populations with different age structures by relating them to a standard population. The current standard population is all persons in the Australian population at 30 June 2001.
cause_name: Standardised death rates (SDRs) enable the comparison of death rates between populations with different age structures by relating them to a standard population. The current standard population is all persons in the Australian population at 30 June 2001.

cause_icd10: Death Rates and Years of Potential Life Lost (YPLL) based on small numbers are volatile and unreliable. SDRs based on less than 20 deaths and crude rates or YPLL based on a very low death count have not been published and appear as 'np'.
cause_name: Death Rates and Years of Potential Life Lost (YPLL) based on small numbers are volatile and unreliable. SDRs based on less than 20 deaths and crude rates or YPLL based on a very low death count have not been published and appear as 'np'.
